name: Mary Berger
text:
Bad place,  they don’t wear gloves when preparing food, and they don’t do delivery because delivery guy
Doesn’t show up.  It’s been 3 years since I’ve been there,  thought I would give them another chance tonight because I can’t get out anywhere.  Nope,  I’m done with them.

name: Misty Swensen
text: Was good, will definitely go again if in Ida Grove

name: Marilyn Kruger
text: Foods good service on the other hand is shall we say Corporate will be getting a call soon.

name: Jennifer Faure
text: I was very disappointed. The only reason I gave it two stars was because the lady at the counter was nice. I wont be going back that's for sure

name: Deb Gross
text: Good buffet and Maeci is so nice employee

name: Dominic Barber
text: I had an ant crawl across my table. Then there were flies. This place was better years ago.

name: Warren S
text: My server was so nice and would check on us often. The food was also great and the bread sticks amazing like Always.

name: kristi hayes
text: Food is normally good here.  On this occasion we arrived 30 min before posted closing time after a baseball game and doors were already locked.

name: Kim Misko
text: My order was bieng delivered when I went to pick it up. But my order was correct. Macie is a hard worker!

name: Reed Wunschel
text:
Amazing food!
Great waiters/waitresses.
Don't miss the chance to feed the geese. It's only $1.00 to get some food to feed the geese. Personally, it's a 10/10.

name: Jeff Walstrom
text: It's a good old fashion pizza hut! A must when in town.

name: Melissa Ox
text: Food wasn't ready on time but we didn't have to wait too long.

text: Good food and good staff

name: joyce buckendahl

name: Jacob Blackman
text: Very cool pizza hut being that it's in the middle of the pond but it's really sub par on the food and the service most of the time

name: E. Mike Durbin
text: Cute! Probably the nicest Pizza Hut I've been too. Yes, I'm a Chicago pizza snob, but I enjoyed our dinner here.

name: Jack Napier
text: Bad food, bad staff, manager yells loud enough for whole restaurant to hear. Plus they use the same cutting tool for sweet and savory choices. Nothing is worse than biting into a cheese pizza and tasting cinnamon sugar.

name: IRONINGOTMC
text: Very nice place and AMAZING breadsticks. You can also buy a bag of bread to throw at the ducks of their dock.

text: Good pizza, good service. Waitresses are kind and courteous, and service was prompt.

text: My 1 year old son and I ordered 1 pizza and a kids spaghetti - after waiting 45 minutes I went up and asked how much longer our food would be. The waitress didn't ring in the spaghetti (which I understand it happens I was a waitress as …More
